claim.claim-text:
A system (200) for use in particle collection and analysis, said system comprising:
an enclosure (206) configured to be attached to a particle-producing device (202), said enclosure including an inlet (208) and an outlet (210);
a filter (212) configured to be coupled to the inlet of said enclosure and configured to filter air directed to said enclosure through the inlet;
a vacuum source (216) configured to be coupled in flow communication with the outlet of said enclosure to generate an aerosol stream from said enclosure to said vacuum source, wherein the aerosol stream includes particles (204) produced by the particle producing device; and
a sampling tower (218) configured to be coupled between said vacuum source and said enclosure outlet, said sampling tower including at least one sampling nozzle (220) extending into said sampling tower and configured for sampling the aerosol stream from said enclosure to said vacuum source.

A method for collection and analysis of particles from a particle producing source enclosed within an enclosure (206) having an inlet (208) and an outlet (210), said method comprising:
supplying filtered air into the enclosure through the inlet;
extracting, with a vacuum source (216), an aerosol stream including particles from the particle-producing source through the outlet (210) ;
directing the aerosol stream from the outlet (210) of the enclosure to the vacuum source (216) via a sampling tower (218), the sampling tower including at least one nozzle (220) for sampling the aerosol stream;
detecting, with a detection instrument coupled to the nozzle, at least one characteristic of the particles in the aerosol stream; and
outputting data concerning the detected characteristic of the particles in the aerosol stream to a computing device.
